Sentencas: In this work, a cost-competitive oxide system of Ni-substituted Sr(1-x)Ti(0.5)Pe(0.5)Ni(0.1)O(3-delta) (STFN, x = 0, 0.02, 0.05), is evaluated as Solid Oxide Fuel Cell cathode.
Titulo: Stable, efficient and cost-competitive Ni-substituted Sr(Ti,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of A-site deficiency

Sentencas: All STFN oxides present cubic perovskite structure with maximum conductivities over 22 S/cm in air.
Titulo: Stable, efficient and cost-competitive Ni-substituted Sr(Ti,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of A-site deficiency

Sentencas: The introduction of Sr deficiency yields higher oxygen vacancy and lower thermal expansion coefficient.
Titulo: Stable, efficient and cost-competitive Ni-substituted Sr(Ti,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of A-site deficiency

Sentencas: As a result, the cathode polarization resistance of 0.107 Omega cm(2) is obtained for Sr0.95Ti0.3Fe0.6Ni0.1O3-delta (STFN-95) at 750 degrees C and po(2) = 0.21 atm, with weak oxygen partial pressure dependence.
Titulo: Stable, efficient and cost-competitive Ni-substituted Sr(Ti,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of A-site deficiency

Sentencas: Specially, STFN-95 presents higher stability with slower R-p increasing rate in lower oxygen partial pressure of 0.14 atm than in 0.21 atm, which greatly facilitates the cathode practical application in SOFC stack under high air utilization condition.
Titulo: Stable, efficient and cost-competitive Ni-substituted Sr(Ti,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of A-site deficiency

Sentencas: Finally, a stable operation of 400 h is achieved using STFN-95 cathode on anode supported single cell at 750 degrees C, without showing Sr and other elements diffusions.
Titulo: Stable, efficient and cost-competitive Ni-substituted Sr(Ti,Fe)O3 cathode for solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of A-site deficiency
